Gracchum jure caesum videri. C. Gracchus contra suasit rogationem, 5611 Scipio tenuit.’' (Compare Appian‚ Β. C. i. l4; Cicer0‚ Lael. c. 25.) A Senatus con- sultum was made ac. 460 to this effect: “In reliquum magistratus continuari et eosdem tribunos refici judicare Senatum contra rem publicam esse'’ (Livy, iii. 21). But this Senatus consultum had not the force of a Lex, and it was not observed.
